Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_annotated_glitch(25.10)                        set_annotated_glitch(25.10)

Name
       set_annotated_glitch

Syntax
       set_annotated_glitch

       [-help]

       [-port <string>]

       [-vh_glitch <string>]

       [-vho_glitch <string>]

       [-view <string>]

       [-vl_glitch <string>]

       [-vlu_glitch <string>]

       Allows the ability to annotate glitches at any specified pin/port. This
       command setting will override the VH/VL glitch with the specified value
       on the given point and use that glitch value to propagate downstream.

       If  the  defined  annotated glitch waveforms do not start and end at 0,
       then the software will not consider those waveforms and a warning  will
       be  issued.  In the following example both VL and VH waves should start
       and end with 0.0 values. Since the VH wave is not  ending  at  0,  this
       waveform will be ignored.

       set_annotated_glitch  -vl_glitch {0 0 100e-12 0.01 200e-12 0.04 300e-12
       0.03 600e-12 0} -port dff1/CK -vh_glitch {0 0 100e-12 0.1  200e-12  0.4
       300e-12 0.3 600e-12 0.1} .

       The software does not save (and report) waveforms below 5% of VDD. Con-
       sider for example, the annotated glitch defined on a pin as:

       set_annotated_glitch -port dff1/CK -vh_glitch {0 0 100e-12 0.01 200e-12
       0.04 300e-12 0.03 600e-12 0}

       In  this case, the glitch peak is 0.04 (40mV), which is below 5% of VDD
       (1080mV) - equal to 54mV. Since this annotated glitch waveform peak  is
       very  low, the report_noise command will not report it. However, if the
       failure criteria is lower than 5%, then the software will save and  re-
       port small glitch violations.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -port <string>
              Specifies port or pin names on which you need to apply glitches.

              This parameter works only when setSIMode -enable_glitch_propaga-
              tion true is set in the report_timing flow.

              In  the update_glitch flow, the -enable_glitch_propagation para-
              meter is already set to true.

       -vh_glitch <string>
              Specifies a list of VH glitch wave points. You must  specify  at
              least 3 time value pairs.

       -vho_glitch <string>
              Specifies a list of VHO glitch wave points.

       -view <string>
              Specifies a list of view names.

       -vl_glitch <string>
              Specifies  a  list of VL glitch wave points. You must specify at
              least 3 time value pairs.

       -vlu_glitch <string>
              Specifies a list of VLU glitch wave points.

       Examples
              *

                The following example annotates the specified VL  glitch  wave
                points:

                set_annotated_glitch  -vl_glitch {0 0.0  0.2e-9 0.540 0.405e-9
                0} -vh_glitch {0.1e-9  0  0.205e-9 0.50 0.405e-9 0.200  0.6e-9
                0.0} -port {A}

              * The following command overrides the glitch value at  RIP  with
                the  annotated  glitch, because glitch is annotated at the re-
                ceiver input:

                set_annotated_glitch -vl_glitch {0 0 100e-12 0.1  200e-12  0.4
                300e-12 0.3 600e-12 0} -port seg2/u9/D

                update_glitch

                report_noise -nets seg2/n8

                -------------------------------------------------------------------------

                Peak(mV)  Level  TotalCap(fF)  TotalArea Width(ps) Vdd(mV) Li-
                brary VictimNet

